{
  "stem": "7598.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "She said that we were on my father's passport, and that she was Belgian and her children were Belgian.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "So they let us all through, including her.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And having been able to get us through without any problems because the French were very unsympathetic to Poles, she said to us, stay.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "We will be there in the morning.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think this is relevant because a lot of people ask me, how could your mother have left you with your uncle and aunt?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I know this is the only reason.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Anyway, my mother went back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She stayed the night with my father at Lapan.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the next morning, no taxi ever turned up.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She couldn't find him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She didn't know his name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the worst thing is she didn't know the name of the village-- of the frontier village where they'd crossed.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were absolutely panic-stricken and tried to thumb lift from anybody and said, take me across, take me across.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother told me that she finally found someone who-- I think it was a Frenchman who said, OK, I'll take you across if you say you lost your children, but where did you cross?",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she said, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We waited all day because, of course, one had no, no news or no directive that-- no idea that the taxi wouldn't come back.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We waited all day, and they didn't arrive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember being very concerned.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But as I said, I had the hope that we would eventually meet in Cognac.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "After two nights of waiting at the frontier, we were told by the French, you, you, you've got to go, you know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Go on.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we went to the station hoping there would be trains or cars.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
